<paragraph blockId="28.[810,1420,913,1467]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,971,952,976]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity box="[1300,1420,952,976]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="47.5" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="39.0">39–56 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades lanceolate, hairy on both sides, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="14.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="9.0">9–20 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[911,1033,1020,1044]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. It is identified by its inflorescence with 3–6 alternate branches, 
<quantity box="[1295,1420,1054,1078]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="2.95" valueMax="4.4" valueMin="1.5">1.5–4.4 cm</quantity>
long, with short trichomes and its elliptical and hairy spikelets.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="535" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[810,1420,913,1467]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,921,1161,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species observed scarcely on the native grassland. Considered Endangered in 
<collectingRegion box="[1163,1330,1195,1219]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[810,1420,913,1467]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,1001,1234,1258]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, North (PA and TO states), Northeast (BA and CE states), South (
<collectingRegion box="[1261,1359,1268,1292]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">PR state</collectingRegion>
) and Southeast (except ES state) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
